  "text": "STEP-NC allows specifying machining process rather that tool motion with respect to the machine axes, using the object-oriented concept of workingstep. In fact, the generation of the tool path is performed at the latter stage of the manufacturing chain by a new breed of intelligent controllers called STEP-NC controllers. These controllers are usually classified in three categories [CITATION_1] : I. conventional CNC control using STEP-NC: a translation module, implemented on a PC, converts a STEP-NC program into ISO6983 commands, executable on a traditional CNC machine (see e.g.",
